OpenJDK&#39;s implementation (yes this is implementation-dependent) uses either Knuth&#39;s &quot;Algorithm D&quot;, or the Burnikel-Ziegler Algorithm, depending on how big the divisor and the dividend are. If the divisor is small, or if they are both of similar magnitude, then the former is used. You can see the source code [here][1].

    public BigInteger divide(BigInteger val) {
        if (val.mag.length &lt; BURNIKEL_ZIEGLER_THRESHOLD ||
                mag.length - val.mag.length &lt; BURNIKEL_ZIEGLER_OFFSET) {
            return divideKnuth(val);
        } else {
            return divideBurnikelZiegler(val);
        }
    }

- [Algorithm D][2]
- [Burnikel-Ziegler Algorithm][3]


